<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,1891,2023]" lastBlockId="25.[189,1399,267,365]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer M." box="[189,369,1891,1917]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="223 - 227" refId="ref38659" refString="Ledoyer M. 1970. Mysidaces des herbiers de phanerogames marines de Tulear (Madagascar). Etude systematique et ecologique. Recueil des Travaux de la Station Marine d'Endoume 10: 223 - 227." type="journal article" year="1970">
Ledoyer (
<date box="[300,361,1891,1917]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1970">1970</date>
)
</bibRefCitation>
did not designate any 
<typeStatus box="[622,684,1891,1917]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">types</typeStatus>
from his large amount of material, consisting of 
<specimenCount box="[1235,1395,1891,1917]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="generic">81 specimens</specimenCount>
. It is not known whether the original specimens still exist in any museum collection, but they are absent in the National Museum of Natural History, Paris (
<collectionCode box="[779,875,1961,1987]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<potCollectionCode box="[779,875,1961,1987]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">MNHN</potCollectionCode>
</collectionCode>
), Endoume Marine Station, Marseille, where Michel Ledoyer worked, and the Verona Museum of Natural History, where he deposited many amphipod 
<typeStatus box="[189,255,268,294]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">types</typeStatus>
. However, Ledoyer described in detail and figured well-recognisably a 
<quantity box="[1095,1185,267,294]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
long adult female from “station 24” (
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer M." box="[413,702,302,329]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="223 - 227" refId="ref38659" refString="Ledoyer M. 1970. Mysidaces des herbiers de phanerogames marines de Tulear (Madagascar). Etude systematique et ecologique. Recueil des Travaux de la Station Marine d'Endoume 10: 223 - 227." type="journal article" year="1970">
Ledoyer 
<date box="[521,584,303,329]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1970">1970</date>
: 223–225
</bibRefCitation>
, figs 1–2), and a 
<quantity box="[907,976,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
long male, providing a figure of its antennular peduncle (
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer M." box="[441,669,338,365]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="223 - 227" refId="ref38659" refString="Ledoyer M. 1970. Mysidaces des herbiers de phanerogames marines de Tulear (Madagascar). Etude systematique et ecologique. Recueil des Travaux de la Station Marine d'Endoume 10: 223 - 227." type="journal article" year="1970">
Ledoyer 
<date box="[548,611,338,364]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1970">1970</date>
: 225
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 1d’). No further material on the species is known so far.
</paragraph>
